data.title: Janet Thompson
data.meta_description: Janet Thompson passed away. This is the full obituary where you can share condolences and memories. Published in the Clinton Herald on 2016-11-08.
data.text:
Janet (Johnson) Thompson, 48, of Denver, Colorado (formerly of Clinton, Iowa) passed away on Wednesday, October 12, 2016. Cremation rites have been accorded. A Memorial service will occur at 11:00 a.m. on Saturday, November 12, at Lemke Funeral Homes - South Chapel (2610 Manufacturing Drive). A visitation will occur one hour prior from 10:00 a.m. until time of the Memorial service at the funeral home. Lemke Funeral Homes assisted the family with arrangements.

Janet was born March 17, 1968 in Princeton, Illinois the daughter of Gilbert and Rose (Danielson) Johnson. Janet was a graduate of Clinton High School and St. Ambrose University. Janet served her Country in the U. S. Army.

Janet is survived by three children - Hannah, Isaac and Micah Thompson of Denver, CO; her Mother - Rose Johnson of Fulton, IL; three sisters - Diane (Ted) Erickson of Rockford, IL, Julie (Dan) VanZuiden of Fulton, IL and Jennifer (Greg) Gresens of Wausau, WI; one brother - Jeff (Becky) Johnson of Portage, WI, with six nieces and three nephews.

Preceding Janet in death was her father and one niece.

Fond memories and condolences for Janet's family may be shared at www.lemkefuneralhomes.com, obituary page.

Published on November 8, 2016

When your purchase is complete, a post will be made on the tribute wall of the deceased signifying the planting of a memorial tree.
